erary analysis and writing in an academic context.", "en": "In this course, students will be introduced to a variety of analytic and argumentative strategies in formulating a persuasive academic essay on a literary subject with special attention to close reading and contextual/cultural analysis. We will read, analyze and write about two selected novellas: Metamorphosis (Franz Kafka, 1915) and Lucy (Jamaica Kincaid, 1990) to reflect upon the interrelated questions of narrative techniques, time, space and nested histories of labor and migration in familial and social contexts. The aim of the course is to cultivate critical skills of literary analysis and writing in an academic context."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Course reader; Metamorphosis (Franz Kafka); Lucy (Jamaica Kincaid)", "en": "Course reader; Metamorphosis (Franz Kafka); Lucy (Jamaica Kincaid)"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "80%", "en": "80%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n\n個別指導", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "", "Individual Instruction"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "Paper one, incl. wkshp drafts: 40 ％\nPaper two, incl. wkshp drafts: 40 ％\nAttendance/Responses/Participation: 20 ％\n*To pass the course: completion of all assignments", "en": "Paper one, incl. wkshp drafts: 40 ％\nPaper two, incl. wkshp drafts: 40 ％\nAttendance/Responses/Participation: 20 ％\n*To pass the course: completion of all assignments"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "Tues 2-4pm & by appt", "en": "Tues 2-4pm & by appt"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "18", "en": "18"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "domain": {"ch": "語言訓練\n\n\n、\n\n\n文學與文化研究", "en": "語言訓練\n\n\n、\n\n\n文學與文化研究"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "英文閱讀解析與寫作論述", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "英語溝通與文化跨越", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試", "出席/課堂表現", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "審美欣賞與多元創意", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "自我評量/同儕互評"]}, {"competencies": "人文思維與社會關懷", "rating": "(4)高", "assesme